<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><generator uri="http://jekyllrb.com" version="3.1.3">Jekyll</generator><link href="https://pcolmer.github.io/feed.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /><link href="https://pcolmer.github.io/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><updated>2016-04-28T15:24:40+01:00</updated><id>https://pcolmer.github.io/</id><title>Papillon Productions - Relative History</title><subtitle>Genealogy at your fingertips</subtitle><entry><title>Jekyll 3.1.3 Released</title><link href="https://pcolmer.github.io/news/2016/04/19/jekyll-3-1-3-released/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Jekyll 3.1.3 Released" /><published>2016-04-19T18:26:16+01:00</published><updated>2016-04-19T18:26:16+01:00</updated><id>https://pcolmer.github.io/news/2016/04/19/jekyll-3-1-3-released</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://pcolmer.github.io/news/2016/04/19/jekyll-3-1-3-released/">&lt;p&gt;v3.1.3 is a patch release which fixes the follow two issues:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Front matter defaults may not have worked for collection documents and posts due to a problem where they were looked up by their URL rather than their path relative to the site source&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Running &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;jekyll serve&lt;/code&gt; with SSL enabled was broken due to a bad configuration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Both of these issues have been resolved. For more information, check out &lt;a href=&quot;/docs/history/#v3-1-3&quot;&gt;the full history&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Happy Jekylling!&lt;/p&gt;</content></entry></feed>
